column4: you know what the coolest thing evar is? isolinux. it makes me happy in all sorts of ways.
booting up, as we speak. thefish. we are booted in 3, 2, 1..
when I open a window in nautilus, it opens visibly enough for me to see the window opening, and then immediately closes.
symbol lookup error: /usr/lib/nautilus/extensions-1.0/libgnome-mount-so: undefined symbol: nautilus_file_info_get_drive.
I have to admit, that doesn't sound very encouraging to me ><
nautilus an related things have a star next to them. does that mean anything?
it seems to be doing a bunch of installing off of the hardy heron cd i burned earlier successfully.
I can't. no internet. wifi isn't working and my ethernet port got fried a few fears ago.
if you or anyone else can fix my interwebs, I shall be eternally grateful.
thefish, kousotu, it's going faster than I expected.
kousotu, I respect the philosophy of debian. even if ubuntu no share it. btw, thefish, I'm up to 26%
